cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SI

The paper presents a new algorithm for graph inference using neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The probabilistic perspective and sequential processes used in the algorithm suggest that it may fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of complex message functions and information aggregation processes may also relate to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The application of the algorithm to graph reasoning and prediction tasks may also suggest sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
